ible without having some custom bufferLoader _perhaps_?\n","created_at":"2016-07-14T13:47:02.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9323#issuecomment-232670028","id":232670028,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9323","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDIzMjY3MDAyOA==","updated_at":"2016-07-14T13:47:02.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/232670028","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mkungla\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mkungla\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/15878458?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mkungla","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mkungla\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mkungla","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mkungla\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE1ODc4NDU4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mkungla\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mkungla\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mkungla\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mkungla","type":"User","id":15878458,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mkungla\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mkungla\/orgs"}},{"index":7,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"I think `three.js` handles this quite well. It's rather a matter of how you use `Audio` and `PositionalAudio` in your application. It would be better if you create separate `Audio` entities for your three `mp3` files once and reuse them whenever it's necessary. For background music or lengthy ambient sound you should use an ordinary HTML5 audio element or maybe something like this #11115.\r\n\r\n","created_at":"2017-04-06T10:22:40.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9323#issuecomment-292